---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Cook's by the Ocean"
  description="A heritage-first rebuild of Cook's by the Ocean in South Wellfleet."
>
  <section class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] lg:items-end">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <p class="eyebrow">South Wellfleet, Cape Cod</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-6xl leading-[0.95] text-[var(--color-ink)] sm:text-7xl">
        A quieter,
        <span class="text-[var(--color-sea)]">heritage-first</span>
        return to Cook's.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-[var(--color-muted)]">
        The new site is being rebuilt to feel closer to the historic Cook's
        experience: calmer, more text-forward, and more respectful of the place,
        while still making cottage browsing and photo viewing easier on modern
        screens.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="button-primary" href="/cottages">Browse Cottages</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/photos">View Photos</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] border border-[rgba(34,52,67,0.14)] bg-[linear-gradient(160deg,rgba(253,251,246,0.92),rgba(215,205,184,0.86))] p-8 shadow-[0_24px_65px_rgba(34,52,67,0.10)]">
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-[var(--color-ink)]">Stage 0 foundation</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
          This first milestone establishes the Astro shell, navigation, placeholder
          routes, and content collections before the full cabin and photo migration.
        </p>
        <dl class="grid gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)]">
          <div class="rounded-[1.25rem] bg-white/70 p-4">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">Current facts kept</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1">Email contact, weekly Saturday rhythm, cabin roster, and amenity wording.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-[1.25rem] bg-white/70 p-4">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">Historic spirit restored</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1">Sidebar structure, calmer pacing, and a more archival sense of place.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-14 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
    <a class="feature-card" href="/cottages">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cottages</p>
      <h2 class="feature-title">14 cabins, grouped by size.</h2>
      <p class="feature-copy">The current operational structure remains intact while the browsing experience becomes more legible.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="feature-card" href="/legacy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Archive</p>
      <h2 class="feature-title">Legacy material stays visible.</h2>
      <p class="feature-copy">The archive is permanent and category-based, separate from the current cabin photography.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="feature-card" href="/contact">
      <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
      <h2 class="feature-title">Simple by design.</h2>
      <p class="feature-copy">Email remains primary. The request dates form will be added after the shell and content model are verified.</p>
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>
